<h1>Welcome To My First Website</h1>

Here’s a simple example of a web page with an image using HTML and CSS:

HTML (index.html)
Copy the code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Simple Web Page</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Welcome to My Web Page</h1>
  </header>
  <main>
    <p>This is a simple web page with an image:</p>
    <img src="example.jpg" alt="A beautiful scenery" class="image">
  </main>
  <footer>
    <p>© 2025 My Website</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>

CSS (styles.css)
Copy the code
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  text-align: center;
  background-color: #f4f4f9;
}

header {
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  color: white;
  padding: 1rem;
}

main {
  margin: 2rem;
}

.image {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  border: 2px solid #ddd;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

footer {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  padding: 1rem;
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 0;
  width: 100%;
}

Notes:
Replace "example.jpg" in the HTML with the path to your image file.
Save the HTML and CSS files in the same directory, and open the HTML file in a browser to view the page.
The CSS ensures the image is responsive and styled with a border and shadow for a polished look.
